FBIS4-60508 "drnes102dd_94009" FBIS-NES-94-102 Daily Report 25 May 1994 Palestinian Affairs Hamas Activist Receives `Quasi-Military' Funeral Hamas Activist Receives `Quasi-Military' Funeral TA2505163894 Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew 1400 GMT 25 May 94 TA2505163894 Tel Aviv IDF Radio Hebrew BFN [Report by Arab affairs correspondent Oren Kohen] [Text] In a funeral procession last night, Palestinian policemen carried on their shoulders the body of Jihad 'Asfur, an Islamic Jihad activist who was killed by IDF [Israel Defense Forces] soldiers' fire on 22 May. 'Asfur's funeral was held in Khan Yunus, and he was buried in a quasi-military ceremony. His body was driven to the cemetery on a Palestinian police jeep. Some 30 policemen attended the funeral, and with them were 10 members of the 'Izz-al-Din al-Qassam squads, the Hamas [Islamic Resistance Movement] military arm, who were armed with M-16 rifles. Thousands of Hamas supporters came to the funeral. Four Palestinian policemen carried 'Asfur's body to the grave. According to eye witnesses, one of the policeman even kissed the body before it was buried. The policemen and the Hamas activists fired their guns in the air to salute 'Asfur, as is customary in military funerals. As will be recalled, the Fatah leaders declared that the Palestinian policemen intend to disarm Hamas activists and other armed Palestinians. 'Asfur was killed on 22 May when IDF soldiers fired antitank missiles at a house on the outskirts of Hebron.
